block.documentation:
The Avionics Subsystem provides the computing power and data processing needed to execute the spacecraft’s operations. The Command and Data Handling Unit serves as the central processor, receiving data from the spacecraft’s sensors, executing commands, and distributing data to other subsystems. The Primary Onboard Computer handles critical tasks such as system control, while the Backup Onboard Computer ensures redundancy in the event of a failure.
The Fault Management CSC plays an integral role in monitoring system health and responding to any anomalies. Should an issue be detected, the CSC can trigger corrective actions or isolate faulty components to maintain overall system integrity. Additionally, the Data Storage Unit holds important mission data, including production records and system logs, ensuring it is safely stored for future transmission to ground control.
